textRun.content: Doesn’t like OTR as a Song of the Summer because she doesn’t like country or rap, and because strongly connected to Mason Ramsey (yodeling boy). Still very popular with the kids she babysat.
Song of the Summer 2019 was Ballin Flossin by Chance the Rapper because of her vacation in Michigan.
This summer is more for playlists, lots of Frank Sinatra and classical music. Listening to less music because already on a screen so often and less music is being released.
First heard OTR when studying abroad in the spring 2019, considers it a staple song of the summer because of its popularity and strong positive association with it from time abroad.
Says OTR is representative of the summer but enjoys Billie Eilish’s “Bad Guy” better (so would choose “Bad Guy” is listening alone). OTR is more representative of everyone’s collective experience

No song in particular associated with this summer so far, because hit songs typically come from time in bars and at parties, which is not happening in the global pandemic world. There might be less agreement of what the hit song of 2020 is because the world is in such disarray.
OTR was popular in Italy too, surprising because it was in English, not Spanish or Italian. Songs of the Summer are only good until around July.
First song of the summer in Italy was by an Italian artist. It was about relaxing and going to the beach and more ‘summery’ things.
No song of summer 2020 because not going out or doing the activities where people listen to new music and get songs of the summer.
Definitely *a* song of the summer, not sure it was *the* song of the summer. Blended two popular genres that aren’t typically combined, so appealed to a lot of people.
No specific song of the summer, but a summer playlist that had a lot of upbeat feel-good songs on it.
Listening to similar songs as she was last summer (upbeat) but a particular song of the summer hasn’t really come up.
